It's not easy for threads to beat Twitter.

With such a small user base Twitter is so famous, not because the most powerful and influential people on earth use it but due to the quality content it generates using jokes, sarcasm, wit and news.

Facebook, Instagram and WhatsApp run from content originally written on Twitter, most probably Threads will also run like that unless people completely shut their Twitter account and move to Threads which isn't an easy task to do for anyone.

To run a platform like Threads where you have to express yourself using text, you need high IQ creators and Zuckerberg has the dumbest user base who can't do anything other that posting pics adding filter and doing Mujra in reels.
